class QuickSort:
    def __init__(self, data):
        self.data = data

    def sort(self):
        def partition(left, right):
            mid = (left + right) // 2
            pivot = sorted([(self.data[left], left), (self.data[mid], mid), (self.data[right], right)])[1][1]
            self.data[right], self.data[pivot] = self.data[pivot], self.data[right]
            i = left
            for j in range(left, right):
                if self.data[j] <= self.data[right]:
                    self.data[i], self.data[j] = self.data[j], self.data[i]
                    i += 1
            self.data[i], self.data[right] = self.data[right], self.data[i]
            return i

        def quicksort(left, right):
            if left < right:
                pivot_index = partition(left, right)
                quicksort(left, pivot_index - 1)
                quicksort(pivot_index + 1, right)

        quicksort(0, len(self.data) - 1)
```

The `QuickSort` class is implemented with a constructor to initialize the internal list and a `sort` method that performs the in-place quicksort algorithm with the median-of-three pivot selection. The `partition` function selects the median of three elements as the pivot and partitions the list accordingly. The `quicksort` function recursively sorts the sublists.

